  "overnight": true,
  "slug": "pork-hotpot",
  "source": "This recipe is based on Oksana Putan's and Julia Lisniak's \"Homemade modern Russian cuisine\" book.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Rinse the meat in cold water, dry using paper towels, season with salt, and refrigerate in a sealed container (or wrapped in a film) overnight.",
          "pause": true
        },
        {
          "text": "Preheat oven to 180C.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Peel (if needed) and cut the potatoes into 2 cm cubes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Put the potatoes into a Dutch oven, add salt, 4 bay leaves, a few peppercorns, 1 teaspoon of cumin seeds, and sprinkle olive oil over the potatoes. Thoroughly mix everything.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Bake the potatoes uncovered in the oven for 20 minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the potatoes are baking, cut the meat into 2 cm cubes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Onions:** peel and cut into large dice. **Chiles:** halve, remove the seeds, and thinly slice. **Garlic:** peel and cut into medium pieces. **Carrots:** peel and cut into 1/2 cm half-moons.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Sauté onions, chiles, and garlic on a large frying pan with olive oil, on medium heat, for 2–3 minutes, until transparent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add carrots and cook for 3 more minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the meat, and cook until the meat is white on all sides, stirring often.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Remove the Dutch oven with the potatoes from the oven, and reduce the temperature to 150C. Add the meat with the vegetables to the potatoes, fill the Dutch oven with hot water to about 3/4 of the height of the potatoes and meat, and carefully mix.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Cover the Dutch oven (use tinfoil if you don’t have a lid), put it back into the oven, and cook covered for 50-60 minutes more until the meat is tender.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add more salt to taste.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
